In the following we discuss fermions coupled to Skyrmions. The
full Lagrangian  of this model is the sum of the fermion 
Lagrangian , the Skyrmion Lagrangian 
 and the interaction Lagrangian . In 
this paper we consider fermions in the background of a static Skyrme 
configuration and neglect the backreaction. Therefore, we do not discuss 
the Skyrmion Lagrangian any further, and the interested reader is referred 
to. The interaction Lagrangian  
given by 

 

where  is a convenient 
parameterization of the Skyrme field.
Equation () is the standard parity-invariant manner in which 
fermions couple to a Skyrme field and is also called the Yukawa 
interaction term. 
This Lagrangian was first introduced by
Gell-Mann and Levy (without a fourth order Skyrme term),
. Also see for a discussion
of various different chiral models. Recently, the Lagrangian
() has been discussed by Balachandran et al. 
. 

