As mentioned above, we make the approximation that the Skyrmion is a fixed
static background field, i.e.  we ignore the backreaction of the
fermion fields.
Furthermore, we only consider spherically symmetric
Skyrmions. For , Skyrmions are believed to be spherically symmetric, 
but for  this is no longer true. However, we expect that some generic 
features of the Skyrmion-fermion interaction are not sensitive to the 
precise shape of the Skyrmion. For more details see Sect. 
. 
